article.headline: South Florida 82, South Carolina State 69
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- McHugh Mattis had 18 points, 12 rebounds and a career-high seven blocked shots, leading South Florida to a 82-69 victory against South Carolina State on Friday. The Bulls (2-0) took a one-point lead into the second half, when they hit 16 of 24 shots from the field and all five attempts from beyond the arc. Melvin Buckley also scored 18 points and freshman teammate Adamu Saaka added 12 in his debut for South Florida. Bulls senior Chris Capko had 10, including the first two 3-pointers of his career. Travis Jones had 18 points and five assists to lead South Carolina State (0-2). Brian Mason contributed 12 and Thomas Bookman had 11 for the Bulldogs. South Florida trailed by eight late in the first half, but closed with an 11-2 run for a 37-36 edge at the break. The Bulls were helped by a 13-0 scoring advantage from the free-throw line. The Bulldogs didn't make any free throws until Jones hit the first of three attempts with 7:50 remaining.
